text.tspan: REACTION CONTROL SYSTEM WORKS IN SPACE
UNLIKE GRID FINS, WHICH ONLY WORK IN AN ATMOSPHERE,
RCS WORKS IN A VACUUM. HOWEVER, RCS REQUIRES A
PROPELLANT, WHICH IS EXPENDED; IN ADDITION, REACTION
CONTROL SYSTEMS ARE NOT NEARLY AS POWERFUL AS
THE GRID FINS CONTROL THE BOOSTER BY ANGLING THEMSELVES;
THIS FORCES THE TOP OF THE BOOSTER TO MOVE TO ONE SIDE, WHICH
TILTS THE BOOSTER RELATIVE TO THE AIRFLOW. WITH GRID FINS, THE
BOOSTER IS CAPABLE OF "GLIDING" TENS OF KILOMETERS DURING THE
THRUST VECTOR DOES NOT POINT THROUGH CENTER OF MASS
GRID FINS ARE RETRACTED DURING LAUNCH;
THEY ARE DEPLOYED IMMEDIATELY AFTER STAGE
LATERAL THRUST IS A SIDE EFFECT OF GIMBAL
ENGINE GIMBAL TILTS THE EXHAUST FLOW OF THE
NOZZLE; THIS HAS THE UNAVOIADABLE SIDE EFFECT
OF A SMALL AMOUNT OF LATERAL THRUST. CARE
MUST BE TAKEN TO MINIMIZE LATERAL MOVEMENT
CAUSING AIR TO FLOW AROUND THE GRID FIN INSTEAD
DESPITE BEING DEPLOYED IMMEDIATELY AFTER STAGE
SEPARATION, THEY DO NOT BEGIN TO TAKE EFFECT UNTIL
HOWEVER, THEY DO NOT PROVIDE MUCH CONTROL
AUTHORITY COMPARED TO GRID FINS OR ENGINE GIMBAL.
GRID FINS ARE INEFFECTIVE WHEN TRANSSONIC
GRID FINS ONLY OPERATE IN AIR
ENGINE GIMBAL WORKS WHENEVER THE ENGINE IS PRODUCING THRUST
